<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-06-08T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-06-08T16:00:00-05:00" n="40" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 1/1793: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Haskell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-08T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 8,
                                        1923—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>For Congressman Porter:</p>
                        <p>I am much gratified by the results reported in your telegram of June 6, 5
                            p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>